citations:
    citation-affc-cersei-ii:
        source: source-affc
        properties:
            locator: "Cersei II"
            text_from_source: "She would need to move quickly, as she had when Robert died. This might be the work of Stannis Baratheon, through some catspaw."
            accessed: "2026-03-06"
        notes: "POV: Cersei Lannister. The morning after Tywin's death. Cersei and Tommen attend the funeral at the Great Sept of Baelor on Visenya's Hill. The current High Septon (the biddable old man chosen by Tyrion) meets them. At the funeral, Cersei observes: Kevan Lannister and his son Lancel (pale and ravaged by injury, growing religious), Lord Gyles Rosby (coughing), Grand Maester Pycelle (possibly asleep), the Tyrells — Mace, Lady Olenna (the Queen of Thorns), Lady Alerie, Garlan, and Margaery. Cersei maneuvers: denies Garth Tyrell the master of coin role (appointing Lord Gyles Rosby instead), refuses Mace Tyrell as Hand. Qyburn reports: the gaoler Rugen was a Varys agent, found a pre-Conquest Gardener gold coin (Garth the Twelfth) in his cell, suggesting Tyrell complicity. Qyburn is given Ser Gregor (dying of thickened manticore venom) to study. Kevan demands Cersei yield the regency; she refuses and he departs, hinting knowingly that Jaime is Tommen's father. Cersei plans to appoint Kevan as Hand. Lady Taena Merryweather introduced, offering Myrish intelligence contacts. Cersei appoints Lord Gyles Rosby as master of coin. Ser Lambert Turnberry wears an eyepatch and pledges to find Tyrion."
